tables.alternate_text: Tanner NT, et al. Physician assessment of pretest probability of malignancy and adherence with guidelines for pulmonary nodule evaluation. Chest. 2017;152(2):263ﾅ70.

figures.alternate_text: Flowchart for assessing surgical risk of a new, solid, indeterminate nodule on chest CT, sized 8 mm to 30 mm. The chart begins with assessing surgical risk, branching into low to moderate and high risk categories. Low to moderate risk leads to assessing clinical probability of cancer, categorized as very low, low/moderate, and high. Each category leads to further actions like PET to assess nodule, CT surveillance, non-surgical biopsy, surgical resection, or SBRT/RFA. High risk leads to non-surgical biopsy or CT surveillance, with outcomes like malignant, non-diagnostic, or specific benign, guiding further actions such as specific treatment or chemotherapy.
